Louise Beaudet https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louise_Beaudet 0 Louise Beaudet (December 5, 1859 – December 31, 1947) an actress, singer and dancer for more than 50 years, starred in stage productions ranging from comic opera to Shakespeare, as well as music-hall and vaudeville, and appeared in 66 silent films.
